attributes.title: Physical Stock Verification
attributes.description:
Findings.

·       Physical stock take of all the items at the branch was done on 15/04/2025. The aim was to assess the strength/weakness of internal control systems put in place. Significant variances in stock items would be interpreted as a threat to the safety of the company’s items and vice versa.

·       Notable discrepancies were observed in the following categories:

·       Aggregate bread difference was shortfall of 98 pcs (White Bread) and shortfall of 42 Pcs (Brown Bread).

·       Aggregated polybags difference was excess of 470pcs.

·       Utto difference was excess of 4.11Kgs.

The table below illustrates the findings:

Implications

Minimal stock variances imply strong controls
attributes.recommendation: · Strong controls on Stocks should be adhered to in order to minimize the variances.

value: Bread variance was within limits.
· Bread stock variance is within the acceptable limit.

· In the prior audit report highlighted variations during physical stock verification on.

ü  Packing Materials: Variance of +292 pieces.

ü  Bread Stock: Variance of - 31 pieces.

· The variances noted are as shown in the mixing chart below.

attributes.title: Production and Market Damages
attributes.description:
Findings.

·       Production and market damages were analyzed to determine their rate during production or from market and compare the same with the allowed standards. High production damage rate would suggest product of inferior quality was allowed to the market.

·       Allowed production damages rate is 0.25% of total production and market damage is 0.2% of net sales.

·       Production and market damage rate was analyzed from cash flow date 07/03/2025 - 14/04/2025.

·       It was observed that  production and market damages were within the established limits,  as illustrated below;

Implications

Damages are maintained within the set limit indicating that controls on damages are effective and this does not expose the company to losses.
attributes.recommendation: To adhere to the set quality control parameters within the production process to minimize production damages.

value: To be maintained.
We will maintain controls on production and market damages.

attributes.title: Fuel Consumption (Generator)
attributes.description:
Findings.

·       Fuel consumption tests were carried out to determine if set consumption standards for sales vans were adhered to.

·       Standard fuel consumption for the branch generator was 26.6l/hr.

·       Generator fuel consumption from 01/04/2025 – 15/04/2025 is analyzed on the below table.

·       It was noted that the Manager filled the Generator fuel tank to brim without getting the exact number of litres to refill from KAF.

Implication

The generator consumption was higher than the set standards. The 29.98 liters per hour is higher than the expected rate by 3.38l/hr.
attributes.recommendation: · The manager should refill the generator as per KAF reports.
attributes.remediation_plan: Generator should be refilled using KAF reports to get correct consumption rate.

value: I will monitor to ensure this is implemented.
This noted.

· In the prior audit report163 litres of generator fuel worth Ksh.26, 159 purchased in different dates between December and January was not received at the branch.

·  Over the reviewed period there were no security guard records of fuel deliveries at the branch creating a loophole for records manipulation.

·        Litres per hour which is within the range.

·        No significant variation between physical records and the system records.
